---
# 3DSendai C identifier gate. The client's convention (AGENTS.md) is mixed and
# deliberate: ab_-prefixed snake functions AND types (ab_term, ab_frame),
# AB_UPPER macros/enum-constants, camelBack params/locals, and a *role*-based
# split of file-scope statics — g_ for app-wide state, s_ for module-private.
#
# That g_/s_ split is a role convention, not a C-linkage one: both g_sessions
# and s_led_ready are `static`, so clang-tidy (which only sees linkage) lumps
# them into one category and cannot accept both prefixes — enforcing either
# prefix false-positives the other. So this gate enforces ONLY the rules that
# are unambiguous AND uniformly followed here: UPPER_CASE macros and enum
# constants. Function/type/variable naming (including the g_/s_ roles) stays a
# human/review convention, not a machine rename that would fight the wire/KAT/
# generated-protocol.h contract.
#
# clang-tidy only lints identifiers we declare (HeaderFilterRegex is an explicit
# allowlist of our headers; llvm::Regex is POSIX ERE with no negative lookahead,
# so vendored monocypher/quirc and the generated protocol.h are excluded by
# omission). Foreign libctru symbols are declared elsewhere and never in scope.
Checks: '-*,readability-identifier-naming'
WarningsAsErrors: 'readability-identifier-naming'
HeaderFilterRegex: 'source/(alert|approval|cam|config|crypto|discovery|input|json|mic|net|paircfg|term|termfont|ui)\.h$'
CheckOptions:
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.MacroDefinitionCase
    value: UPPER_CASE
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.MacroDefinitionIgnoredRegexp
    value: '^_.*'
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.EnumConstantCase
    value: UPPER_CASE
...
